<subSubSection id="C30F653F5D5AFF81FF63BDF2333B825E" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D5AFF81FF63BDF2374D83F3" blockId="28.[189,993,593,685]" box="[189,310,659,685]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D5AFF81FF63BDF2374D83F3" bold="true" box="[189,310,659,685]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D5AFF81FF63BDA3333B825E" blockId="28.[189,1398,706,833]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Pale yellow species belonging to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D5AFF81FDB3BDA235788382" authorityName="Grootaert, Cumming &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2007" box="[621,771,706,733]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicaput">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D5AFF81FDB3BDA235788382" box="[621,771,706,733]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. flavicaput</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. Occiput dark yellowish in ground-colour. One pair of distinct vertical bristles. No acrostichals. Hind tibia with only 3 long bristles on apical half.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30F653F5D5AFF81FF63BC46341082BF" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
