<emphasis id="B961EAA65D5AFF81FF63BC46372D821F" bold="true" box="[189,342,807,833]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D5AFF81FF63BC373756822E" blockId="28.[189,597,854,947]" box="[189,301,854,880]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<collectingCountry id="F30276245D5AFF81FF63BC373752822E" box="[189,297,854,880]" name="Thailand" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Thailand</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D5AFF81FF63BCF9342E82ED" blockId="28.[189,597,854,947]" box="[189,597,920,947]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D5AFF81FF63BCF9342E82ED" bold="true" box="[189,597,920,947]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Habitat and seasonal occurrence</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D5AFF81FF63BCA6341082BF" blockId="28.[189,619,967,1059]" box="[189,619,967,993]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">River banks in bamboo forest, April.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30F653F5D5AFF81FF63BB6832F085C7" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D5AFF81FF63BB683754857D" blockId="28.[189,619,967,1059]" box="[189,303,1033,1059]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D5AFF81FF63BB683754857D" bold="true" box="[189,303,1033,1059]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D5AFF81FF63BB5932F085C7" blockId="28.[189,1398,1080,1178]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D5AFF81FF63BB5937B7850C" authorityName="Grootaert, Cumming &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2007" box="[189,460,1080,1106]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D5AFF81FF63BB5937B7850C" box="[189,460,1080,1106]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Chersodromia obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D5AFF81FDB7BB59357B850C" authorityName="Grootaert, Cumming &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2007" box="[617,768,1080,1106]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicaput">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D5AFF81FDB7BB59357B850C" box="[617,768,1080,1106]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. flavicaput</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having only 3 long bristles on the hind tibia while the latter has 5 bristles. In addition 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D5AFF81FDB4BB3D3496852B" authorityName="Grootaert, Cumming &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2007" box="[618,749,1115,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D5AFF81FDB4BB3D3496852B" box="[618,749,1115,1142]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a pair of distinct vertical bristles, no acrostichals, stronger male cerci, longer spines on left surstylus, and tip of phallus is less coiled.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
